-- Ghana 91-day bill yield rises to 24.0787 pct
-- By Kwasi Kpodo
-- Fri May 02, 2014 12:38PM EDT
-- None



ACCRA, May 2 (Reuters) - The Bank of Ghana said on Friday the yield on its 91-day bill rose to a fresh three-year high of 24.0787 percent at its May 2 auction from 24.0589 percent at the last auction.

The Bank said 530.31 million cedis ($189.6 million) worth of bids for the 91-day paper were accepted at the auction out of a total 537.1 million cedis of bids tendered.  For full details please click here:   http://www.bog.gov.gh/privatecontent/Treasury/Auctresults%201379.pdf